      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>
	  Success! [In the year ... ] of King
	  <persName key="pers:VpŚrīPuḷumāvi">Vāsiṣṭhīputra Svāmi Śrī Puḷumāvi</persName>, the gṛhapati 
	  <persname key="pers:Am-Kahutara">Kahutara</persname>
	  of the Piṇḍasutariya family and
	  <persName key="pers:Am-Isila">Isila</persName>, the son of the
	  gṛhapati
	  <persName key="pers:Am-Puri">Puri</persName>, together with 
	  his brothers and sisters and his wife
	  <persName key="pers:Am-Nākānikā">Nākānikā</persName> (and) ... 
	  together with his sons, have ereceted as their pious 
	  gift (this) Dharma Chakra (Sacred Wheel) on the western
	  gateway (of the railing) owned by the Buddhist Community of the
	  Chetikiya Sect of the Mahā-Chaitya.
	</p>
